text: "Ain't No Mountain High Enough" is a 1967 song by Marvin Gaye and Tammi Terrell. It was taken from their album United. ==Diana Ross solo version== In 1970, Diana Ross covered "Ain't No Mountain High Enough" for her first studio album. It went to number 1 in the United States, number 6 in the United Kingdom, number 14 in the Netherlands and Ireland, number 31 in Australia and number 11 in Canada. It was nominated for a Grammy Award in 1971. == References == Category:1967 songs Category:Soul songs Category:Marvin Gaye songs Category:The Supremes songs Category:The Temptations songs Category:Diana Ross songs Category:Jimmy Barnes songs Category:Michael McDonald (musician) songs Category:Jimmy Somerville songs
